    <thetext>In basic and formal reviews, it&apos;s is possible by anybody with access to the review group to write anomalies, 
if this user was not part of the review, he/she gets automatically added to the review.
 
 However for informal reviews. creation of anomalies is restricted to pre-selected participants.
 there is really no reason to prevent this as the person can add him/her self at any time.
 
Automatic addition of participant will simplify the process of participation for formal reviews, with no sacrifice on functionality.</thetext>
